    "Heard {vet} describe the kids they buried at DISRUPTR and knew the war back in {home} had started keeping a ledger {vet} couldn't close.",   // 396
    "Learned {vet} had hauled one of {home}'s small sayings into the wreckage of DISRUPTR and kept it alive out there where nothing else of theirs survived.",   // 397
    "Saw {vet} call DISRUPTR a mirror and not look away from it, and started counting the quarters until there'd be nothing of the kid from {home} left in the reflection.",   // 398
    "Heard {vet} explain that beating MEGACORP meant burying their own, and understood the unicorn the papers loved was a thing {vet} was bleeding to feed.",   // 399
    "Learned what {vet} was really chasing under all the funding rounds — {dream} — and ached, because the war was raising the price of it every quarter back in {home}.",   // 400
    "Heard the company's word — churn — come out of {vet}'s mouth for the dead, and swore to be the one place left where {vet} still had to call them children.",   // 401
    "Understood the dead intern {vet} couldn't put down was really {trauma} wearing a stranger's face, and put a hand on the weight {vet} had been hauling out of {home} alone.",   // 402
    "Watched {vet} take a stranger child's nametag home like kin, and recognized in it the same care {vet} once couldn't show the living back in {home}.",   // 403
    "Heard {vet} describe beating SYNERGY by out-fighting their own reflection three campuses deep, and stopped pretending the company was making {vet} into anything but the next thing to be killed.",   // 404
    "Learned that the kitchen back in {home} had walked through SYNERGY's campuses in {vet}'s head when nothing else could, and felt the old house had reached the war after all.",   // 405
    "Heard {vet} name themselves the monopoly out loud and not look away, and decided to be the one piece of {home} the tower couldn't refinance — to keep the booth set until {vet} couldn't find their way back to it.",   // 406
    "Took {dream} into safekeeping the night {vet} admitted the pivot was eating it, and made the door back in {home} into a vault for the one part of {vet} the war couldn't be allowed to spend.",   // 407
    "Saw {vet} pick up the key before the headline that called them a monopoly, and held onto the order of it — door first, tower second — as proof the kid from {home} was still making the choice.",   // 408
    "Took into safekeeping the bad joke {fallen} told before every drop, because {vet} couldn't be the only one carrying a dead friend the company had already churned off a slide.",   // 409
    "Filled a third bowl for {fallen} beside {vet} and let it steam and die, because the war had stolen even the grieving and someone back in {home} had to give it back.",   // 410
    "Sat the long silence over the empty seat for {fallen} with {vet}, and understood the war had finally made {vet} into someone who knew how to grieve at a table back home.",   // 411
    "Heard {vet} fear the day the company's gentle words for slaughter were all {vet} had, and made the counter back in {home}'s reach the place where the plain words still had to be said.",   // 412
    "Learned what {vet} had done to not be the one cut in that first review — {crime} — and chose to keep no ledger but the one that ended with {vet} alive at the counter back home.",   // 413
    "Realized {vet} hadn't been asked a single honest question since shipping out, and resolved to keep being the one at the counter who knew {vet} from before the company's words.",   // 414
    "Watched {vet} let a single bowl run slow with no number at the end of it, and saw the war's clock loosen its grip on the kid from {home} for the length of one cooling broth.",   // 415
    "Heard {vet} chase the runway toward {dream} and had to say the unbearable thing — that {dream} was sitting right there at the counter back in {home}'s reach, and {vet} kept burning past it.",   // 416
